data.description: As a member of the meerkat community and a part of African wildlife this is highly offensive. Meerkats at the Kalahari desert make it their goal to make our burrows feel comfortable as well as not get eaten by hawks. Comparing specific meerkats to girls from a sorority is absurd and beyond inaccurate. Making the claim that sorority girls pose like meerkats in pictures is demeaning the values of eating grass as a water source that we were founded on. This clearly is a stab at a species in the desert that does nothing but support the rest of the food chain.
